# Creating Virtual Environment Using Virtualenv
- Download the get_pip.py file
- Optional (Install python if your are not installed before)
- Then run it command prompt(as administrator),by using command: python get_pip.py
- Now you can install virtualenv y using : pip install virtualenv
- After installing virtualenv, create virtualenvironments by using : virtuaenv env_name
- Then activate env_name by using : env_name\Scripts\activate
- If you want to deactivate ev_name by using : deactivate
